    "patch": "@@ -24,6 +24,16 @@ This article provides information about the latest releases and change announcem\n \n ## August 2025\n \n+### Public preview - Lifecycle Workflows task now supports setting Access Package assignments expiration\n+\n+**Type:** New feature      \n+**Service category:** Lifecycle Workflows    \n+**Product capability:** Identity Governance  \n+\n+Customers can now configure the remove all access packages task in Lifecycle Workflows to automatically expire access packages assignments after a specified number of days when employees leave the organization. For more information, see: [Remove all access package assignments for user](../id-governance/lifecycle-workflow-tasks.md#remove-all-access-package-assignments-for-user).\n+\n+---\n+\n ### Plan for change - New end user homepage in My Account\n \n **Type:** New feature      "

ai_summary.Response: The commit includes several updates to Microsoft Entra ID documentation. Notably, a new feature for Lifecycle Workflows is announced, allowing for the configuration of access package assignments expiration. Additionally, numerous entries in the SaaS applications section have been modified, primarily to update author and reviewer details, indicating ongoing maintenance and corrections within the documentation.
